{"expireTime":9007200809748944000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-caf5340b46946e795391aa91fcbee8c4-gatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-autolink-headers-","val":"<h1 id=\"using-shader-modules\"><a href=\"#using-shader-modules\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using Shader Modules</h1>\n<h2 id=\"usage\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h2>\n<p>To add/inject existing modules into your shaders, just add the modules parameter to your <code class=\"language-text\">assembleShaders</code> call:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>shaderModule<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'library-of-shader-modules'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>vs<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> fs<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> getUniforms<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> moduleMap<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">assembleShaders</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>gl<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  fs<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'...'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  vs<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'...'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  modules<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>shaderModule<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>To configure the shader module uniforms:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">const {vs, fs, getUniforms, ...} = assembleShaders(gl, {..., modules: [...]});\n\n// create a program with the returned shaders using your preferred WebGL library\n\nconst uniforms = getUniforms(props);\n\n// set returned uniforms on the program using your preferred WebGL library</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"glsl-versions-and-shader-module-transpilation\"><a href=\"#glsl-versions-and-shader-module-transpilation\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GLSL Versions and Shader Module Transpilation</h2>\n<p>Shader Modules are automatically converted (\"transpiled\") to the version of the shader you are importing them into.</p>\n<h2 id=\"shader-code-injection\"><a href=\"#shader-code-injection\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Shader Code Injection</h2>\n<p>By using the <code class=\"language-text\">inject</code> parameter, code can be injected into existing shaders.</p>"}